#Steps to Install Retropie onto Raspberry Pi 5
1. Once SSH’d into the Raspberry Pi on your terminal, install the needed packages to run the Retropie script by running the command: 
“sudo apt install git lsb-release”
2. Download the latest Retropie setup script by running the commands:
“cd
git clone --depth=1 https://github.com/RetroPie/RetroPie-Setup.git”
3. Execute the script by running the commands:
“cd RetroPie-Setup
chmod +x retropie_setup.sh
sudo ./retropie_setup.sh”
4. The screen below should be displayed. Select the “Basic install” option and wait until complete.
![Install Screen](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10035308/16218285/f06f3ba8-3738-11e6-9ccc-be601172713b.png)
5. Upon completion, you can install additional packages by selecting the “Manage packages” option and downloading specific packages.  






